def update_password(db: Session, email: str, new_password: str):
    user = get_user_by_email(db, email)
    if user:
        user.hashed_password = hash_password(new_password)
        db.commit()
        return True
    return False

def create_instrument(db: Session, instrument: schemas.InstrumentCreate, manager_id: int):
    db_instrument = models.Instrument(
        serial_number=instrument.serial_number,
        model=instrument.model,
        manufacturer=instrument.manufacturer,
        department=instrument.department,
        technician=instrument.technician,
        frequency=instrument.frequency,
        calibration_date=instrument.calibration_date,
        notes=instrument.notes,
        manager_id=manager_id,
    )
    db.add(db_instrument)
    db.commit()
    db.refresh(db_instrument)
    return db_instrument

def create_technician(
    technician: schemas.TechnicianCreate,
    db: Session = Depends(get_db),
    current_user: schemas.UserResponse = Depends(get_current_user),
):
    existing_email = db.query(models.Technician).filter(models.Technician.email == technician.email).first()
    if existing_email:
        raise HTTPException(status_code=400, detail="Technician with this email already exists")
    existing_phone = db.query(models.Technician).filter(models.Technician.phone == technician.phone).first()
    if existing_phone:
        raise HTTPException(status_code=400, detail="Technician with this phone number already exists")
    db_tech = models.Technician(**technician.model_dump(), manager_id=current_user.id)
    db.add(db_tech)
    db.commit()
    db.refresh(db_tech)
    return db_tech
